The '''Centre for Medieval Studies''' at the [[University of Bergen]], [[Norway]] was founded in 2003 by the [[Research Council of Norway]]. 

The organization's site defines its goal as follows: "to enhance our understanding of Europe as a whole, in the Middle Ages as well as today, from a peripheral point of view".  

It is headed by [[Sverre Bagge]].

