'''Maba Man''' (Traditional: 馬壩人, simplified: 马坝人 pinyin: mǎbà-rén) is the pre-modern hominid whose remains were discovered in 1958 in caves near the town called [[Maba, Guangdong|Maba]], near [[Shaoguan]] city in the north part of [[Guangdong]] province, [[China]].<ref name="LS">{{cite web|url=http://www.livescience.com/17130-ancient-human-head-trauma.html|title=Ancient Human's Head Trauma Points to Foul Play|last=Welsh|first=Jennifer|publisher=Live Science|accessdate=17 January 2012}}</ref><ref>''Wu R. K.'' et ''Pang R.-C.'' Fossil human skull of early Paleoanthropic stage found at Mapa, Shaoquan,KwantungProvince// Vertebrata PalAsiatica, 1959, t.3, №1, pp.176-182.</ref>
The Maba Men lived in caves at Lion Rock, near Maba.<ref name="LS"/> The site is now a park and tourist attraction including the possibility to visit the cave and a museum nearby.
Although described at the site as "ape-men", the Maba Men were not really very apelike and were comparable to [[Europe]]an [[Neanderthal]]s.
